<TITLE> 72 reported missing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, May 25 (bdnews24.com)At least 72 people have been reported missing in Char Fashion, Sadar and Monpura Upazilas of Bhola during the tidal surge induced by cyclone 'Aila'. The Upazila Nirbahi Officer of Char Fashion, Mostafa Kamal, told bdnews24.com that over 50 people went missing as their houses were washed away by the wind-fed surge. Kamal said none of them could be rescued until now. Local Awami League leader Jahirul Islam told bdnews24.com that two childrenRussell, 12 and Mizan, 10were missing. Monpura Upazila chairman Nazir Ahmed said three trawlers carrying passengers sank in the Meghna estuary in the onslaught of the storm in which 20 people went missing. The rescue operation was going on in cooperation with local administration, Nazir said The deputy commissioner of Bhola, Mezbahul Islam, told bdnews24.com that over 300 houses were damaged at Char Pata, Char Khalifa, and Syedpur unions. The deputy director of Cyclone Preparedness Programme of Red Crescent Society, Bhola zone, Bashir Ahmed, told bdnews24.com that Dal Char, Char Kukrimuri, Char Patila, Char Hasina, Char Nizam and Char Kachchpia of Char Fashion Upazila were now under 8-10 feet water. The body of one Nazimuddin, 25, was recovered on Monday morning in the trawler-sinking incident, Ahmed said The inhabitants of these chars were being evacuated to safer places, Bashir said The executive engineer of Water Development Board Md Ferdous said a vast land area was inundated after the dams at Sakuria of Monpura Upazila and Char Madras of Char Fashion Upazila got damaged. bdnews24.com/c
